description:
The Bagelry is a local independent shop. If you wake up early, you'll find the folks in the back cooking up the bagels ready to serve the morning and daytime crowds. The bagels ($1/each) have a good crisp, firm exterior and a soft chewy interior. Just what I expect from a fresh bagel. There's an assortment of flavors (sesame, cinnamon raisin, blueberry, egg, plain, poppy seed, etc)  to choose from too. So,

If you're in need of a carbo fix - get a bagel;
If you want to add an indulgent spread - buy one of the grab & go containers of cream cheese which appear in an assortment of colors and flavors (saves time);
If you want more of a sandwich - order one of the lox and cream cheese, egg or other variety of sammie.

On the weekend, this is a great spot to bring your coffee or beverage from the neighboring Peet's or Starbucks and enjoy freshly made food. This is the least expensive food on the block. Dogs enjoy sitting in the patio out front. So do folks who people watch or read the newspaper. What's not to love?
